      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That frustration is deeply understandable because confronting absolute meaninglessness can indeed turn life into a cruel joke. Many philosophers and scientists have wrestled with this exact feeling, realizing that the lack of a cosmic purpose actually frees us to define our own unique value in the present moment. Instead of viewing entropy as a punisher, consider it the very condition that makes our fleeting creation meaningful now.",
      "source": "target",
